primary.context: Caller wanted instructions on what to do with their rental agreement
primary.detail: The agent offered to send the link and asked if there was anything else, but never confirmed the link was actually sent.

steps: Caller asked about rental agreement instructions.
Agent performed account lookup and identity verification.
Agent explained the purpose of the rental agreement.
Agent offered to send a link via email and phone.
Caller accepted, but agent moved to closing without confirming the send action.

failure.detail: Agent moved to closing script before confirming the rental link was actually sent to the user.

actions.detail: Offered link but never confirmed execution of send

insights.summary: The caller wanted to know how to handle a rental agreement. The agent verified the caller and offered to send a link, but ended the call without confirming the link was sent.
insights.verbatim: Would you like a link sent to your email and phone so you can complete the agreement online?
insights.coaching: The agent must confirm the delivery of the link (e.g., 'I have sent that link now') before asking if there is anything else and ending the call.
